Reasoning: The paper deals with constraint satisfaction problems (CSPs) and their efficient decidability using symmetric polymorphisms. This falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of polymorphisms also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and the study of logical reasoning (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for solving CSPs, which further supports these categories.
